results.prompt_sent: I'm starting work on a dark mode feature for our app. Set up everything I need to track this work: create a project for it, then create a workunit inside that project for the implementation work. The workunit should have a clear problem statement and success criteria that you derive from the feature context.

arguments.name: Dark Mode Feature
arguments.description: Implementation of dark mode theme for our application to improve readability in low-light conditions and reduce eye strain.

results.task_name: Break down a feature into tasks
results.prompt_sent: I need to implement user notifications for workunit updates. Think about what steps are actually needed to build this end-to-end, then create a workunit called "Implement User Notifications" and add all the implementation tasks to it. Be thorough — this is a real feature, not a toy example.

arguments.problem_statement: Build a comprehensive notification system that keeps users informed about relevant workunit activities including creation, updates, completions, assignments, and comments. The system should support multiple delivery channels (in-app, email), user preferences for notification types and frequency, real-time updates, and proper notification management (mark as read, dismiss, archive).
arguments.success_criteria: Users receive timely notifications for all relevant workunit events through their preferred channels. System supports granular user preferences, handles high-volume notification generation efficiently, provides a clean notification center UI, and includes proper error handling and retry logic for failed deliveries.
